managed account,


63
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,554 line:-2
the profiles
installed on the device,


64
00:02:33,587 --> 00:02:35,856 line:-2
and how VPN is configured
in Settings.


65
00:02:38,058 --> 00:02:41,195 line:-2
VPN & Device Management
have been combined together,


66
00:02:41.228 --> 00:02:43.297 line:-2 align:center
providing
one comprehensive place


67
00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:45.465 line:-1 align:center
to display the device state.


68
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:47,568 line:-2
There, you can get
a complete understanding


69
00:02:47.601 --> 00:02:51.171 line:-2 align:center
of how your device
is being managed.


70
00:02:51,205 --> 00:02:54,274 line:-2
Another key component
of MDM is installing apps.


71
00:02:54,308 --> 00:02:57,611 line:-2
Many MDM vendors have an agent
app that they require


72
00:02:57.644 --> 00:02:59.813 line:-1 align:center
as part of configuring devices,


73
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:02,449 line:-2
or perhaps an organization
has a critical app


74
00:03:02.482 --> 00:03:04.318 line:-1 align:center
all their employees need.


75
00:03:04.351 --> 00:03:06.987 line:-2 align:center
On supervised devices,
this isn't a problem


76
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:11,024 line:-2
because apps install
without prompting the user.


77
00:03:11.058 --> 00:03:14.361 line:-2 align:center
However, unsupervised devices
prompt for permission


78
00:03:14.394 --> 00:03:18.498 line:-2 align:center
to install apps, which
the user could then decline.


79
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:21,935 line:-2
Wouldn't it be great if you
had more control over this?


80
00:03:21,969 --> 00:03:25,005 line:-1
Well, now you do.


81
00:03:25.038 --> 00:03:27.441 line:-1 align:center
Introducing Required App.


82
00:03:27.474 --> 00:03:30.744 line:-2 align:center
You can now specify one app that
you would like to be installed


83
00:03:30.777 --> 00:03:32.646 line:-1 align:center
on unsupervised devices.


84
00:03:32.679 --> 00:03:35.682 line:-2 align:center
We ensure user privacy
is protected,


85
00:03:35.716 --> 00:03:38.385 line:-2 align:center
since the user
is consenting to the app install


86
00:03:38.418 --> 00:03:40.087 line:-1 align:center
during MDM enrollment,


87
00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:41.688 line:-2 align:center
and only this app
will install


88
00:03:41.722 --> 00:03:43.824 line:-2 align:center
without additional
user approval.


89
00:03:43.857 --> 00:03:47.227 line:-2 align:center
Simply add the iTunes Store ID
of the App Store application


90
00:03:47.261 --> 00:03:49.730 line:-1 align:center
to the MDM profile.


91
00:03:49.763 --> 00:03:52.933 line:-2 align:center
Then ensure your app has
a device or user license


92
00:03:52.966 --> 00:03:55.636 line:-2 align:center
and send the InstallApplication
command.


93
00:03:55,669 --> 00:03:57,971 line:-2
Also make sure to add
a managed app attribute


94
00:03:58.005 --> 00:04:01.275 line:-2 align:center
to ensure the user
cannot remove your app.


95
00:04:01.308 --> 00:04:03.210 line:-2 align:center
Securing the flow of data
between apps


96
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:06,613 line:-2
is also a really
important consideration.


97
00:04:06,647 --> 00:04:09,449 line:-2
Managed open-in allows you
to control whether data


98
00:04:09.483 --> 00:04:12.486 line:-2 align:center
is allowed to enter or leave
the management sphere.


99
00:04:12.519 --> 00:04:16.056 line:-2 align:center
At its most basic, it controls
independently whether data can


100
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:17,691 line:-2
can be sent
from an unmanaged app


101
00:04:17.724 --> 00:04:20.260 line:-2 align:center
to a managed app
and vice versa.


102
00:04:20.294 --> 00:04:22.896 line:-2 align:center
And now we're making
it better than ever


103
00:04:22,930 --> 00:04:25,199 line:-1
with managed pasteboard.


104
00:04:26.533 --> 00:04:29.770 line:-2 align:center
A new restriction called
requireManagedPasteboard


105
00:04:29,803 --> 00:04:34,575 line:-2
controls whether copy/paste is
affected by managed open-in.


106
00:04:34.608 --> 00:04:36.810 line:-2 align:center
System apps that will
honor the restriction


107
00:04:36,844 --> 00:04:40,914 line:-2
include Calendar,
Notes, Mail, and Files.


108
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:43,550 line:-2
All other apps require
no additional changes


109
00:04:43.584 --> 00:04:46.720 line:-1 align:center
to adopt this feature.


110
00:04:46,753 --> 00:04:49,423 line:-2
Like usual,
apps installed via MDM


111
00:04:49.456 --> 00:04:51.658 line:-2 align:center
will automatically be
treated as managed,


112
00:04:51,692 --> 00:04:55,863 line:-2
and apps installed by the user
will be treated as unmanaged.


113
00:04:55.896 --> 00:04:58.365 line:-2 align:center
With managed pasteboard,
you'll always be allowed


114
00:04:58.398 --> 00:05:00.267 line:-1 align:center
to see the paste button.


115
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,102 line:-2
If you're not allowed
to paste content somewhere


116
00:05:02.135 --> 00:05:04.171 line:-2 align:center
due to the restriction,
you'll get


117
00:05:04,204 --> 00:05:06,740 line:-2
a "Paste Not Allowed"
notification.


118
00:05:06,773 --> 00:05:09,243 line:-2
As a side note,
the organization name


119
00:05:09,276 --> 00:05:12,246 line:-2
that appears in the notification
can be modified using


120
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:15,349 line:-2
the OrganizationInfo Settings
command.


121
00:05:15.382 --> 00:05:18.218 line:-2 align:center
Last year, we brought Shared
iPad to Business,


122
00:05:18,252 --> 00:05:21,021 line:-2
which allows employees to have
a personal experience


123
00:05:21.054 --> 00:05:22.923 line:-1 align:center
on a shared device.


124
00:05:22,956 --> 00:05:25,058 line:-2
Shared iPad has traditionally
required


125
00:05:25,092 --> 00:05:28,495 line:-1
the use of a Managed Apple ID,


126
00:05:28,529 --> 00:05:32,165 line:-2
but with Temporary Session,
anyone can use a shared iPad.


127
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:36,003 line:-2
When logging out, all data,
such as Safari browsing history,


128
00:05:36.036 --> 00:05:38.939 line:-2 align:center
modified user settings,
and files added


129
00:05:38.972 --> 00:05:40.774 line:-1 align:center
will be deleted from the device,


130
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:43,610 line:-2
leaving it
ready for the next user.


131
00:05:43.644 --> 00:05:47.614 line:-2 align:center
In iOS 14.5, we have introduced
three new features


132
00:05:47.648 --> 00:05:52.019 line:-2 align:center
in the SharedDeviceConfiguration
Settings command.


133
00:05:52,052 --> 00:05:55,455 line:-2
TemporarySessionOnly is
to limit the ability to log in


134
00:05:55.489 --> 00:05:57.824 line:-1 align:center
with a Managed Apple ID.


135
00:05:57.858 --> 00:06:00.861 line:-2 align:center
TemporarySessionTimeout
and UserSessionTimeout


136
00:06:00.894 --> 00:06:04.665 line:-2 align:center
will automatically log the user
out after a set amount of time,


137
00:06:04,698 --> 00:06:06,834 line:-2
ensuring that your data
is secure


138
00:06:06.867 --> 00:06:09.703 line:-1 align:center
after a period of inactivity.


139
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:12,639 line:-2
Make sure to not set
the timer to a value too short,


140
00:06:12.673 --> 00:06:15.409 line:-2 align:center
and also pressing the power
or Home button


141
00:06:15,442 --> 00:06:17,945 line:-2
will cause
the timer to reset.


142
00:06:17.978 --> 00:06:19.446 line:-2 align:center
Now let's talk about
some changes


143
00:06:19.479 --> 00:06:22.249 line:-1 align:center
